#. <section class="sutta" id="sn11.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.13:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.13:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13. Mahālisutta → mahāli (sattavatapada) suttaṃ (bj) | devasuttaṃ (3) (s1) | tatiyadevasuttaṃ (s2, s3) | devā (3) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Mahālisutta"
msgstr "13. With Mahāli"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn11.13:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "sn11.13:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mahāli licchavī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahāli "
"licchavī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Mahāli the Licchavi went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:2.1"
msgid "“Diṭṭho kho, bhante, bhagavatā sakko devānamindo”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, have you seen Sakka, lord of gods?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:3.1"
msgid "“Diṭṭho kho me, mahāli, sakko devānamindo”ti."
msgstr "“I have, Mahāli.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:4.1"
msgid "“So hi nūna, bhante, sakkapatirūpako bhavissati."
msgstr "“But surely, sir, you must have seen someone who looked like Sakka."

msgctxt "sn11.13:4.2"
msgid "Duddaso hi, bhante, sakko devānamindo”ti."
msgstr "For Sakka is hard to see.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Sakkañca khvāhaṃ, mahāli, pajānāmi sakkakaraṇe ca dhamme, yesaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"samādinnattā sakko sakkattaṃ ajjhagā, tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Mahāli, I understand Sakka. And I understand the things that he undertook "
"and committed to, which enabled him to achieve the status of Sakka."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.496"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:6.1"
msgid ""
"Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo pubbe manussabhūto samāno magho nāma māṇavo "
"ahosi, tasmā maghavāti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he was a brahmanical student "
"named Magha. That’s why he’s called Maghavā."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:7.1"
msgid ""
"Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo pubbe manussabhūto samāno sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ adāsi, "
"tasmā sakkoti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he gave gifts carefully. "
"That’s why he’s called Sakka, the careful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:8.1"
msgid ""
"Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo pubbe manussabhūto samāno pure dānaṃ adāsi, tasmā "
"purindadoti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he gave gifts in stronghold "
"after stronghold. That’s why he’s called Purindada, the stronghold-giver."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:9.1"
msgid ""
"Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo pubbe manussabhūto samāno āvasathaṃ adāsi, tasmā "
"vāsavoti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he gave the gift of a guest "
"house. That’s why he’s called Vāsava, the houser."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:10.1"
msgid ""
"Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo sahassampi atthānaṃ muhuttena cinteti, tasmā "
"sahassakkhoti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Sakka thinks of a thousand things in a moment. That’s why he’s called "
"Sahassakkha, Thousand-Eye."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:11.1"
msgid ""
"Sakkassa, mahāli, devānamindassa sujā nāma asurakaññā pajāpati, tasmā "
"sujampatīti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Sakka’s wife is the demon maiden named Sujā. That’s why he’s called "
"Sujampati, Sujā’s husband."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.231"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:12.1"
msgid ""
"Sakko, mahāli, devānamindo devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ "
"kāreti, tasmā devānamindoti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"Sakka rules as sovereign lord over the gods of the Thirty-Three. That’s why "
"he’s called lord of gods."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.497"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:13.1"
msgid ""
"Sakkassa, mahāli, devānamindassa pubbe manussabhūtassa satta vatapadāni "
"samattāni samādinnāni ahesuṃ, yesaṃ samādinnattā sakko sakkattaṃ ajjhagā."
msgstr ""
"In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he undertook seven vows. And "
"it was because of undertaking these that he achieved the status of Sakka."

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.2"
msgid "Katamāni satta vatapadāni?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.3"
msgid "Yāvajīvaṃ mātāpettibharo assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I support my parents. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.4"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ kule jeṭṭhāpacāyī assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I honor the elders in the family. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.5"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ saṇhavāco assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I speak gently. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.6"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ apisuṇavāco assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I not speak divisively. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.7"
msgid ""
"yāvajīvaṃ vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvaseyyaṃ muttacāgo "
"payatapāṇi vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato, "
msgstr ""
"As long as I live, may I live at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely "
"generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to "
"give and to share. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.8"
msgid "yāvajīvaṃ saccavāco assaṃ, "
msgstr "As long as I live, may I speak the truth. "

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.9"
msgid ""
"yāvajīvaṃ akkodhano assaṃ—sacepi me kodho uppajjeyya, khippameva naṃ "
"paṭivineyyanti."
msgstr ""
"As long as I live, may I be free of anger, or should anger arise, may I "
"quickly get rid of it."

msgctxt "sn11.13:13.10"
msgid ""
"Sakkassa, mahāli, devānamindassa pubbe manussabhūtassa imāni satta "
"vatapadāni samattāni samādinnāni ahesuṃ, yesaṃ samādinnattā sakko sakkattaṃ "
"ajjhagāti."
msgstr ""
"In a former life, when Sakka was a human being, he undertook seven vows. And "
"it was because of undertaking these that he achieved the status of Sakka."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:14.1"
msgid "Mātāpettibharaṃ jantuṃ,"
msgstr "A person who respects their parents,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:14.2"
msgid "kule jeṭṭhāpacāyinaṃ;"
msgstr "and honors the elders in the family,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:14.3"
msgid "Saṇhaṃ sakhilasambhāsaṃ,"
msgstr "whose speech is gentle and courteous,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:14.4"
msgid "pesuṇeyyappahāyinaṃ."
msgstr "and has given up divisiveness;"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.13:15.1"
msgid "Maccheravinaye yuttaṃ,"
msgstr "who’s committed to getting rid of stinginess,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:15.2"
msgid "saccaṃ kodhābhibhuṃ naraṃ;"
msgstr "is truthful, and has mastered anger:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:15.3"
msgid "Taṃ ve devā tāvatiṃsā,"
msgstr "the gods of the Thirty-Three"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.13:15.4"
msgid "āhu sappuriso itī”ti."
msgstr "call them truly a good person.”"
